## Branding & Attribution Requirement

This section is a condition of the license grant above, not a separate
recommendation. Using, deploying, or distributing the Software, or any
derivative work based on it, is conditioned on compliance with the
following:

1. **Fixed navigation branding.** The "FPGA Vision Remote Lab" logo/wordmark
   and the Hochschule Bonn-Rhein-Sieg logo, as they appear in the
   navigation bar shipped with the Software, must remain visible,
   unmodified, and undiminished (no resizing, recoloring, hiding, or link
   removal) in every deployment, including deployments run by third
   parties under their own name or organization. They may not be removed,
   replaced, or obscured.

2. **Additive "In partnership with" list.** The "In partnership with"
   section on the landing page lists institutions associated with this
   project, starting with the Hochschule Bonn-Rhein-Sieg. A party that
   deploys the Software under their own organization may append their own
   institution's logo to this list, but may never remove, hide, or
   otherwise diminish the logos already present in the list at the time
   they obtained the Software.

3. **Enforcement.** These are conditions of the copyright license granted
   above, not merely requests. A deployment that violates them falls
   outside the scope of this license and constitutes copyright
   infringement; the rights granted above terminate automatically for any
   party that fails to comply, until and unless the violation is cured.

Requests to deviate from these requirements (for example, white-labeling
without attribution) require prior written permission from the copyright
holder.
